10. Delivering Audit-Ready Systems 
An effective SSoW should be: 
• Clear – Easily understood by those doing the work 
• Practical – Usable in live environments 
• Compliant – Meets regulatory requirements 
• Traceable – Demonstrates decision-making and controls 
• Verified – Proven to work in practice 
 
11. Conclusion 
SSoW assurance is not about documentation—it is about confidence in safe delivery. 
Organisations that succeed: 
• Focus on real-world application 
• Prioritise engagement over paperwork 
• Use audits as a tool for improvement, not just compliance 
Operational Assurance Group’s approach ensures that: 
• Systems are built for reality 
• Audits are meaningful 
• Outcomes are practical and sustainable 
 
12. Final Thought 
A safe system of work is only effective when the person doing the job understands it, trusts it, and 
uses it. 
 
 

